revised_title: Anatomical Analysis of a Monstrous Double Cat
tldr: Dr. Mullen presents a detailed account of the dissection of a monstrous double cat, focusing on its unique anatomical features and internal organs. The cat had two bodies joined at the navel, four hind legs, two tails, two anuses, and two pudenda. The study provides insights into the development and structure of such monstrosities and contributes to the understanding of animal physiology.
scientific_discipline: Biology and Life Sciences > Anatomy and Embryology
